<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authorityName="González-Rodríguez &amp; Short" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Notionotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notionotus bicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Notionotus bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the bicolorous dorsal coloration that can also be observed in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. garciae" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="garciae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. garciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. patamona" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="patamona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. patamona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. lohezi" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="lohezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. lohezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be recognized by the shape of the aedeagus, the median lobe is much shorter than in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. insignitus" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="insignitus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. insignitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aedeagi of Notionotus lohezi species group A N. bicolor (holotype) B N. insignitus (holotype) C N. brunbadius (holotype) D N. patamona (holotype) E N. retusus (holotype) F N. lohezi (paratype) G N. juma (holotype) H N. garciae (holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.80775.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709485" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">8B</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. patamona" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="patamona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. patamona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aedeagi of Notionotus lohezi species group A N. bicolor (holotype) B N. insignitus (holotype) C N. brunbadius (holotype) D N. patamona (holotype) E N. retusus (holotype) F N. lohezi (paratype) G N. juma (holotype) H N. garciae (holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.80775.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709485" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">8D</figureCitation>
), and slightly longer than in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. lohezi" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="lohezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. lohezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aedeagi of Notionotus lohezi species group A N. bicolor (holotype) B N. insignitus (holotype) C N. brunbadius (holotype) D N. patamona (holotype) E N. retusus (holotype) F N. lohezi (paratype) G N. juma (holotype) H N. garciae (holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1109.80775.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/709485" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">8F</figureCitation>
). The margins of the median lobe are sinuate with a widening in the middle length, this differs in the other species where the margins are slightly straight. Moreover, the apex is slightly narrow and rounded, this differs in 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. insignitus" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="insignitus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. insignitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with acute apex, 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. patamona" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="patamona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. patamona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with rounded and wide apex and 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. lohezi" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="lohezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">N. lohezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with blunt apex.
</paragraph>
